Pereonites 1–7 dorsally smooth. Gnathopod 1 subchelate; coxa large, about as long as coxa 2, subrectangular, with concave anterior margin, distally straight; basis moderately setose along anterior margin; ischium short; carpus compressed, shorter than propodus, with narrow posterior lobe; propodus small, margins subparallel, sparsely setose along posterior margin, palm transverse, entire, straight. Gnathopod 2 minutely chelate;
propodus palm moderately obtuse
. Pereopod 4 coxa with a well-developed posteroventral lobe. Pereopod 5 basis slightly broader than long, not posteroproximally excavate, posterior margin weakly serrate. Pereopod 7 basis posterodistally produced less than halfway along merus.
